Reginald Fox https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reginald_Fox 0 Reginald Fox (22 December 1881, Stoke Newington, London – 3 May 1943, Harefield, Middlesex) was a British actor. He appeared with Louise Maurel and John Hamilton in a dramatic short film, The Whistler (released December 1926), directed by Miles Mander, and made in the Phonofilm sound-on-film system.
